#: ../../source/postgis/metatables.rst:35
msgid ""
"Geography and Geometry are similar in that they can both represent the same "
"type of spatial data, but differ in a few crucial ways:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/postgis/metatables.rst:37
msgid ""
"The Geometry column type can hold geometric data of any type and in any (or "
"no) projection and CRS. It is not optimized for dealing with geodetic "
"measurements (distances on the sphere)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/postgis/metatables.rst:38
msgid ""
"The Geography type, while able to handle geodetic measurements, are much "
"more limited, in that all coordinates are assumed to be WGS84 (4326) and "
"there are fewer compatible functions when compared to Geometry."
msgstr ""

